race.comment: FACTUALLY (3) comes here following two narrow defeats at Yarra Valley and Bendigo, finishing 0.4L behind the winner on both occasions. She was favourite there last start in a very similar race to this. Soft track is a query, but she's on song and shapes to get her chance. PROPHET'S CHOICE (7) was trending the right way before a disappointing performance at Hamilton last time out. She's on the quick turnaround today and drops back to the 1000m journey where she was very good three back at Colerain. Can bounce back today. SOMAURUM (5) comes across from South Australia where she has turned in some solid outings, namely two back at Penola. They look to have found the right race for her today though with the blinkers on first time. Expecting a better run back in trip. STIRRUP (10) is not out of this if he can run up to his latest performance.
